{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":556,"text":"It's a great time to be a molecular biologist. (Laughter)"},{"time":3994,"text":"Reading and writing DNA code is getting easier"},{"time":6876,"text":"and cheaper."},{"time":8408,"text":"By the end of this year, we'll be able to sequence"},{"time":10578,"text":"the three million bits of information"},{"time":12282,"text":"in your genome in less than a day"},{"time":15252,"text":"and for less than 1,000 euros."},{"time":17662,"text":"Biotech is probably the most powerful"},{"time":20492,"text":"and the fastest-growing technology sector."},{"time":23516,"text":"It has the power, potentially,"},{"time":26818,"text":"to replace our fossil fuels,"},{"time":29035,"text":"to revolutionize medicine,"},{"time":31252,"text":"and to touch every aspect of our daily lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35463,"text":"So who gets to do it?"},{"time":39295,"text":"I think we'd all be pretty comfortable with"},{"time":41790,"text":"this guy doing it."},{"time":45062,"text":"But what about"},{"time":46977,"text":"that guy? (Laughter)"},{"time":49849,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51719,"text":"In 2009, I first heard about DIYbio."},{"time":57193,"text":"It's a movement that -- it advocates making biotechnology"},{"time":61306,"text":"accessible to everyone,"},{"time":63387,"text":"not just scientists and people in government labs."},{"time":67026,"text":"The idea is that if you open up the science"},{"time":70566,"text":"and you allow diverse groups to participate,"},{"time":73369,"text":"it could really stimulate innovation."},{"time":75062,"text":"Putting technology in the hands of the end user"},{"time":77868,"text":"is usually a good idea because they've got the best idea"},{"time":81057,"text":"of what their needs are."},{"time":83160,"text":"And here's this really sophisticated technology"},{"time":86297,"text":"coming down the road, all these associated"},{"time":89041,"text":"social, moral, ethical questions,"},{"time":91738,"text":"and we scientists are just lousy at explaining to the public"},{"time":95129,"text":"just exactly what it is we're doing in those labs."},{"time":99011,"text":"So wouldn't it be nice"},{"time":101739,"text":"if there was a place in your local neighborhood"},{"time":104175,"text":"where you could go and learn about this stuff,"},{"time":106755,"text":"do it hands-on?"},{"time":109078,"text":"I thought so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110593,"text":"So, three years ago, I got together"},{"time":112473,"text":"with some friends of mine who had similar aspirations"},{"time":116010,"text":"and we founded Genspace."},{"time":118145,"text":"It's a nonprofit, a community biotech lab"},{"time":121601,"text":"in Brooklyn, New York,"},{"time":122955,"text":"and the idea was people could come,"},{"time":124724,"text":"they could take classes and putter around in the lab"},{"time":128697,"text":"in a very open, friendly atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132809,"text":"None of my previous experience prepared me"},{"time":135450,"text":"for what came next. Can you guess?"},{"time":138795,"text":"The press started calling us."},{"time":141523,"text":"And the more we talked about how great it was to increase"},{"time":144641,"text":"science literacy, the more they wanted to talk"},{"time":147313,"text":"about us creating the next Frankenstein,"},{"time":150441,"text":"and as a result, for the next six months,"},{"time":153446,"text":"when you Googled my name,"},{"time":155223,"text":"instead of getting my scientific papers, you got this."},{"time":159276,"text":"[\"Am I a biohazard?\"]"},{"time":160854,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":162987,"text":"It was pretty depressing."},{"time":164778,"text":"The only thing that got us through that period"},{"time":167738,"text":"was that we knew that all over the world,"},{"time":169599,"text":"there were other people that were trying to do"},{"time":171185,"text":"the same thing that we were."},{"time":173121,"text":"They were opening biohacker spaces, and some of them"},{"time":175625,"text":"were facing much greater challenges than we did,"},{"time":178266,"text":"more regulations, less resources."},{"time":182383,"text":"But now, three years later, here's where we stand."},{"time":186582,"text":"It's a vibrant, global community of hackerspaces,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and this is just the beginning."},{"time":192902,"text":"These are some of the biggest ones,"},{"time":194963,"text":"and there are others opening every day."},{"time":197027,"text":"There's one probably going to open up in Moscow,"},{"time":199898,"text":"one in South Korea,"},{"time":201197,"text":"and the cool thing is they each have their own"},{"time":203523,"text":"individual flavor"},{"time":205306,"text":"that grew out of the community they came out of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207630,"text":"Let me take you on a little tour."},{"time":210769,"text":"Biohackers work alone."},{"time":213217,"text":"We work in groups,"},{"time":215777,"text":"in big cities — (Laughter) —"},{"time":220162,"text":"and in small villages."},{"time":222832,"text":"We reverse engineer lab equipment."},{"time":225600,"text":"We genetically engineer bacteria."},{"time":228136,"text":"We hack hardware,"},{"time":230363,"text":"software,"},{"time":232608,"text":"wetware,"},{"time":235032,"text":"and, of course, the code of life."},{"time":237968,"text":"We like to build things."},{"time":240903,"text":"Then we like to take things apart."},{"time":247290,"text":"We make things grow."},{"time":249406,"text":"We make things glow."},{"time":251208,"text":"And we make cells dance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255175,"text":"The spirit of these labs, it's open, it's positive,"},{"time":258966,"text":"but, you know, sometimes when people think of us,"},{"time":261407,"text":"the first thing that comes to mind is bio-safety,"},{"time":265434,"text":"bio-security, all the dark side stuff."},{"time":268511,"text":"I'm not going to minimize those concerns."},{"time":271119,"text":"Any powerful technology is inherently dual use,"},{"time":274916,"text":"and, you know, you get something like"},{"time":276133,"text":"synthetic biology, nanobiotechnology,"},{"time":279983,"text":"it really compels you, you have to look at both"},{"time":282607,"text":"the amateur groups but also the professional groups,"},{"time":286020,"text":"because they have better infrastructure,"},{"time":288471,"text":"they have better facilities,"},{"time":290019,"text":"and they have access to pathogens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292518,"text":"So the United Nations did just that, and they recently"},{"time":295798,"text":"issued a report on this whole area,"},{"time":298406,"text":"and what they concluded was the power of this technology"},{"time":301478,"text":"for positive was much greater than the risk for negative,"},{"time":305330,"text":"and they even looked specifically at the DIYbio community,"},{"time":308859,"text":"and they noted, not surprisingly, that the press"},{"time":312404,"text":"had a tendency to consistently overestimate our capabilities"},{"time":316428,"text":"and underestimate our ethics."},{"time":318963,"text":"As a matter of fact, DIY people from all over the world,"},{"time":322492,"text":"America, Europe, got together last year,"},{"time":325222,"text":"and we hammered out a common code of ethics."},{"time":327771,"text":"That's a lot more than conventional science has done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331131,"text":"Now, we follow state and local regulations."},{"time":334779,"text":"We dispose of our waste properly, we follow"},{"time":336775,"text":"safety procedures, we don't work with pathogens."},{"time":340116,"text":"You know, if you're working with a pathogen,"},{"time":342819,"text":"you're not part of the biohacker community,"},{"time":345363,"text":"you're part of the bioterrorist community, I'm sorry."},{"time":348516,"text":"And sometimes people ask me,"},{"time":350439,"text":"\"Well, what about an accident?\""},{"time":352326,"text":"Well, working with the safe organisms that we normally"},{"time":355884,"text":"work with, the chance of an accident happening"},{"time":359243,"text":"with somebody accidentally creating, like,"},{"time":361571,"text":"some sort of superbug,"},{"time":363217,"text":"that's literally about as probable as a snowstorm"},{"time":367467,"text":"in the middle of the Sahara Desert."},{"time":369539,"text":"Now, it could happen,"},{"time":370893,"text":"but I'm not going to plan my life around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375049,"text":"I've actually chosen to take a different kind of risk."},{"time":377979,"text":"I signed up for something called the Personal Genome Project."},{"time":381091,"text":"It's a study at Harvard where, at the end of the study,"},{"time":383563,"text":"they're going to take my entire genomic sequence,"},{"time":386331,"text":"all of my medical information, and my identity,"},{"time":390003,"text":"and they're going to post it online for everyone to see."},{"time":394145,"text":"There were a lot of risks involved that they talked about"},{"time":397075,"text":"during the informed consent portion."},{"time":398851,"text":"The one I liked the best is,"},{"time":400734,"text":"someone could download my sequence, go back to the lab,"},{"time":404579,"text":"synthesize some fake Ellen DNA,"},{"time":406873,"text":"and plant it at a crime scene. (Laughter)"},{"time":410947,"text":"But like DIYbio, the positive outcomes and"},{"time":415477,"text":"the potential for good for a study like that"},{"time":418623,"text":"far outweighs the risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420675,"text":"Now, you might be asking yourself,"},{"time":423076,"text":"\"Well, you know, what would I do in a biolab?\""},{"time":426513,"text":"Well, it wasn't that long ago we were asking, \"Well,"},{"time":429842,"text":"what would anyone do with a personal computer?\""},{"time":432907,"text":"So this stuff is just beginning."},{"time":434871,"text":"We're only seeing just the tip of the DNA iceberg."},{"time":438747,"text":"Let me show you what you could do right now."},{"time":441832,"text":"A biohacker in Germany, a journalist, wanted to know"},{"time":445667,"text":"whose dog was leaving little presents on his street?"},{"time":448901,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":451811,"text":"Yep, you guessed it. He threw tennis balls"},{"time":454517,"text":"to all the neighborhood dogs, analyzed the saliva,"},{"time":457779,"text":"identified the dog, and confronted the dog owner."},{"time":461673,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":467949,"text":"I discovered an invasive species in my own backyard."},{"time":471253,"text":"Looked like a ladybug, right?"},{"time":473193,"text":"It actually is a Japanese beetle."},{"time":475241,"text":"And the same kind of technology --"},{"time":477152,"text":"it's called DNA barcoding, it's really cool --"},{"time":479236,"text":"You can use it to check if your caviar is really beluga,"},{"time":484102,"text":"if that sushi is really tuna, or if that goat cheese"},{"time":487335,"text":"that you paid so much for is really goat's."},{"time":490749,"text":"In a biohacker space, you can analyze your genome"},{"time":494650,"text":"for mutations."},{"time":495942,"text":"You can analyze your breakfast cereal for GMO's,"},{"time":499166,"text":"and you can explore your ancestry."},{"time":502084,"text":"You can send weather balloons up into the stratosphere,"},{"time":504441,"text":"collect microbes, see what's up there."},{"time":508063,"text":"You can make a biocensor out of yeast"},{"time":510494,"text":"to detect pollutants in water."},{"time":512681,"text":"You can make some sort of a biofuel cell."},{"time":516313,"text":"You can do a lot of things."},{"time":518606,"text":"You can also do an art science project. Some of these"},{"time":521996,"text":"are really spectacular, and they look at social,"},{"time":525637,"text":"ecological problems from a completely different perspective."},{"time":528323,"text":"It's really cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529885,"text":"Some people ask me, well, why am I involved?"},{"time":532903,"text":"I could have a perfectly good career in mainstream science."},{"time":536998,"text":"The thing is, there's something in these labs"},{"time":539526,"text":"that they have to offer society that you can't find"},{"time":542185,"text":"anywhere else."},{"time":544152,"text":"There's something sacred about a space where"},{"time":546830,"text":"you can work on a project, and you don't have to justify"},{"time":549342,"text":"to anyone that it's going to make a lot of money,"},{"time":552216,"text":"that it's going to save mankind, or even that it's feasible."},{"time":555471,"text":"It just has to follow safety guidelines."},{"time":558398,"text":"If you had spaces like this all over the world,"},{"time":561254,"text":"it could really change the perception"},{"time":563486,"text":"of who's allowed to do biotech."},{"time":566018,"text":"It's spaces like these that spawned personal computing."},{"time":569710,"text":"Why not personal biotech?"},{"time":572126,"text":"If everyone in this room got involved,"},{"time":574503,"text":"who knows what we could do?"},{"time":576251,"text":"This is such a new area, and as we say back in Brooklyn,"},{"time":580011,"text":"you ain't seen nothin' yet. (Laughter)"},{"time":583291,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}